            <title>[JDK-8311862] RISC-V: small improvements to shift immediate instructions</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8311862</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>We sometimes emit this code in risc-v backend:&lt;br/&gt;
slli Rd, Rs, 0&lt;br/&gt;
(for example we do this in String.IndexOf intrinsic)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
it&amp;#39;s an equivalent of addi Rd, Rs, 0 ( a synonym for mv Rd, Rs)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
addi with 0 has higher chances to be just a register renaming in decoder and not utilise ALU.&lt;br/&gt;
We observed some positive effect of replacing slli by 0 with addi on hifive.</description>
